  "prompt": "What should I do if every afternoon I feel sleepy at the office?",
  "response": "Here are some strategies to combat afternoon sleepiness:\n\n1. Sleep hygiene\n- Ensure you get 7-9 hours of quality sleep nightly\n- Maintain a consistent sleep schedule\n- Create a comfortable sleep environment\n\n2. Diet and nutrition\n- Eat a balanced lunch with protein and complex carbohydrates\n- Avoid heavy, high-carb meals that cause energy crashes\n- Stay hydrated\n- Limit caffeine intake after noon\n\n3. Workplace strategies\n- Take short breaks and walk around\n- Do light stretching\n- Get some natural sunlight\n- Keep your workspace well-lit\n- Use a standing desk periodically\n\n4. Physical activity\n- Exercise regularly, especially in the morning\n- Take short walks during breaks\n- Do quick desk exercises\n\n5. Manage energy levels\n- Practice stress management techniques\n- Consider power naps (10-20 minutes) if possible\n- Use caffeine strategically\n- Adjust your work schedule if flexible\n\n6. Medical considerations\n- Check for underlying health issues like sleep apnea\n- Consult a doctor if sleepiness persists\n- Review any medications that might cause drowsiness\n\n7. Additional tips\n- Listen to upbeat music\n- Engage in stimulating work during peak drowsy times\n- Use cold water or mint to stay alert",
